Big Brother Naija ex-housemate Bamike Olawunmi-Adenibuyan aka Bam Bam has confirmed she is expecting a second child. The reality TV star recently revealed that she is expecting her second child with her husband of two years, Teddy A. In a series of photos shared via her page, Bam Bam expressed the joy of motherhood. “No one else will ever know the strength of my love for you. After all, you and your sister are the only ones who know what my heart sounds like from the inside. Being a mother is learning about the strength you didn’t know you had and dealing with fears you didn’t know existed,” she captioned some of the photos.   PHOTOS: ASUU meets to announce decision on proposed strike     ASUU keeps students, govt in suspense     NSCDC warns fuel marketers against hoarding, hiking price   - Advertisement - She featured her husband and reality TV star Teddy A in some of the photos. Bam Bam and Teddy A welcomed their first child in 2020. The couple became an item after their stint at the third season of Big Brother Naija and they went on to tie the knot in 2019. They had a very beautiful wedding ceremony in Dubai which was attended by friends and family of the couple. SPONSORED